        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 25. Paragiopagurus acutus (De Saint Laurent, 1972), holotype male (SL 5.6 mm), Philippines, USNM 168309: a, shield and cephalic appendages; b, right antennal peduncle, lateral; c, left cheliped, dorsolateral; d, right cheliped; e, chela of same, mesial; f, right 2nd pereopod, lateral; g, dactyl of same, mesial; h, propodus and dactyl of left 4th pereopod, lateral; i, left 2nd pleopod, lateral; j, telson. Scales = 2 mm (a,c-g), and 1 mm (b,h,j)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4659131/files/figure.png" .

